<!-- 1.2.48 -->
<div class='toload proposition'>
<p><span class='envidentifier'>Proposition 1.2.48</span>
Let $S$ be a distributive inverse semigroup and $s,t,z,a\in S$.
<ol class='alphpar'>
	<li> If $(t\setminus s)$ exists, then $(zt)\setminus(zs)$ exists and is equal to $z(t\setminus s)$. Similarly, $(tz)\setminus(sz)$ exists and is equal to $(t\setminus s)z$.</li>
	<li> If $t\land z$, $s\land z$ and $(t\setminus s)$ exist, then
		<div class='equation'>\[
		(t\land z)\setminus(s\land z)=(t\setminus s)\land z,
		\]</div>
		in the sense that these elements exist and are equal.</li>
	<li>If $a\leq s\lor t$, and $a\setminus s$ exists, then $a\setminus s\leq t$.</li>
	<li>If $a\setminus s$ and $a\setminus t$ exist, and $s\leq t$, then $a\setminus t\leq a\setminus s$.</li>
</ol>
</p>
</div>